        public static <T> Stream<T> stream(java.util.Iterator<? extends T> $receiver)

        Converts an iterator into a stream.

        Be cautious: this assumes the iterator is finite and so returns a interface Stream. If not so, assign the result to a interface Stream to avoid errors.
